Yearly Rolling Mean

The first thing we will look at is how the sales (measured both in dollars and volume sold) change as a function of time from 2012 until the last avaliable data. Since we are interested in long term trends we will look at the data with an exponential weighted moving average with a 90 day halflife. We have two different types of graphs shown below, one that plots each year individually and one that plots the entire trend.

In all four plots we can see that the amount sold increases overall as a function of time. This trend is more obvious for the sales in dollars than the sales in volume. This result is expected since we expect the market to grow every year.

However, if you look at this year when compared with previous years there is a much larger increase. This hints that this year is special and that Covid-19 did have a measurable effect on the industry. In order to see this more clearly one needs to look at other aspects of the data. The precentage growth each year would tell us for sure whether or not this year is an outlier.
